== Use Cases
- An in-place wiki for any repository
  - All the source files are pages
- A wiki from a directory of texts
- XLog blogging

== Players/Roles
- Content - this is a set of files.
  - any directory
  - a project repository
  - a set of cogwiki serializations
- CogBase - this is the canonical data.
  - It is built from the files and from their repo, if any.
  - You can rebuild a CogBase from Content later.
- CogWiki - Web/CLI/REST UI for static views of CogBase
  - Talks to the CogBase
  - Updates the Content.

== Rules/Priciples
- Each wiki has one canonical cogbase
  - Possibly upstream
- All web content is statically cached

